  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Factory Supervisor",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Job Summary</strong></h3><p>The Production Supervisor is responsible for directly supervising shop-floor workers and machines to ensure daily production activities are carried out according to the production plan. The role focuses on manpower control, machine operation, discipline, and immediate problem-solving on the factory floor.</p><h3><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Supervise operators and helpers to ensure assigned tasks are completed correctly</p></li><li><p>Ensure machines are operated as per standard procedures and production instructions</p></li><li><p>Maintain discipline, attendance, and proper use of safety equipment</p></li><li><p>Record daily production output, defects, and downtime</p></li><li><p>Immediately report breakdowns, quality issues, or manpower shortages to the Production Manager</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Required Qualifications</strong></h3><ul><li><p>3-year Diploma in Textile Technology or relevant textile field</p></li><li><p>Experience working as a supervisor or senior operator in a textile factory</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Required Skills & Competencies</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Strong shop-floor supervision and people-handling skills</p></li><li><p>Practical knowledge of textile machines and processes</p></li><li><p>Ability to handle workers and resolve day-to-day production issues</p></li><li><p>Basic reporting and record-keeping skills</p></li><li><p>Awareness of safety and quality requirements</p></li></ul>",
